Got it! You want your **Gallery** to **default show MOR Number in descending order** (highest first), while still supporting sorting on all other columns. Here's the complete setup for **SharePoint**.

---

## **1️⃣ App.OnStart**

```powerfx
// Default sort column = MOR Number
Set(Gl_varSortColumn, "cr4e0_mor_number");

// Default sort order = Descending
Set(varSortOrder, SortOrder.Descending);
```

This ensures the gallery **initially loads with descending MOR Number**.

---

## **2️⃣ Gallery Items Formula**

```powerfx
SortByColumns(
    Search(
        Filter(
            nfGoLiveForum,
            (engagement_type = gl_dllEngagementType_1.Selected.Value 
                || IsBlank(gl_dllEngagementType_1.Selected.Value))
            && DateValue(target_implementation_date) > GL_Fromdate_1.SelectedDate
            && DateValue(target_implementation_date) <= GL_Todate_1.SelectedDate
        ),
        Gl_txtSearch_1.Text,  // Search box text
        "mor_number",
        "project_name",
        "go_live_change_request_1",
        "sponsoring_accountable_cio_name",
        "analyst_name",
        "column6_dummy",
        "column7_dummy",
        "column8_dummy",
        "column9_dummy",
        "column10_dummy"
    ),

    // Sort column based on selected header
    Switch(
        Gl_varSortColumn,
        "cr4e0_mor_number",                "mor_number",
        "cr4e1_project_name",              "project_name",
        "cr4e2_go_live_change_request_1",  "go_live_change_request_1",
        "cr4e3_sponsoring_accountable_cio_name", "sponsoring_accountable_cio_name",
        "cr4e4_analyst_name",              "analyst_name",
        "cr4e5_column6_dummy",             "column6_dummy",
        "cr4e6_column7_dummy",             "column7_dummy",
        "cr4e7_column8_dummy",             "column8_dummy",
        "cr4e8_column9_dummy",             "column9_dummy",
        "cr4e9_column10_dummy",            "column10_dummy",
        "mor_number" // default sort
    ),

    // Sort order variable
    varSortOrder
)
```

✅ **Explanation**:

* If search box is blank → shows **all records**
* Gallery initially sorted **MOR Number DESC**
* Clicking any column icon → toggles ASC/DESC

---

## **3️⃣ Sort Icon OnSelect Example**

For **MOR Number column**:

```powerfx
Set(Gl_varSortColumn, "cr4e0_mor_number");
Set(
    varSortOrder,
    If(varSortOrder = SortOrder.Descending, SortOrder.Ascending, SortOrder.Descending)
);
```

For other columns, just change `"cr4e0_mor_number"` to the column key, e.g., `"cr4e1_project_name"`.

